- Prevent malformed JSON responses when Sentry API permission errors occur

## Changes

### Bug Fixes
- Add try-catch blocks to `createOtelLookupTool` and `createDatasetAttributesTool` 
- Catch `UserInputError` exceptions and return them as parseable error strings
- Preserve the original error messages from UserInputError for better context

This prevents the JSON parsing errors that were occurring when 403 permission errors were thrown during AI tool execution. The tools now return error messages that the AI agent can understand and either retry with different parameters or pass meaningful errors back to the user.

